Augustine Ehikioya, Abuja  Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, SAN, will be representing President Muhammadu Buhari at an Extraordinary ECOWAS summit holding on Friday in Niamey, Niger Republic. The Summit, which will include other ECOWAS Heads of State and Government, will review the ongoing situation in Guinea Bissau. The Vice President, according to a statement by the Senior Special Assistant on Media and publicity, Laolu Akande, will depart Abuja and return later on Friday.